# SaveDataDebugPanelSystem

## Purpose
ImGui debug panel demoing the save-data save/load flow. Reads the engine `SaveDataSingletonComponent`
to list the existing slots and, for the selected slot, shows an editable JSON text buffer. "Load"
refreshes the buffer from the in-memory slot; "Save" parses the buffer and emits a
`SetSaveDataRequestOneFrameComponent` (slot UUID + parsed JSON) for the engine to apply and persist.
"New slot" seeds the buffer with an empty object under a freshly generated UUID.

Panel state (selected slot, edit buffer) lives in ECS as `SaveDataPanelStateSingletonComponent`, seeded
once from the first available slot. Like the other debug panels, the system no-ops when the savedata
singleton is absent and guards every ImGui call so the Testing build (no ImGui context) emits no
request.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SaveDataSingletonComponent | read | Source of the slot list and per-slot JSON shown in the panel |
| SaveDataPanelStateSingletonComponent | write | Presence-check; created lazily, then updated as the user edits |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SaveDataPanelStateSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Holds the selected slot UUID and the editable JSON buffer |
| SetSaveDataRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted on Save with the slot UUID + parsed JSON |
